column5: Ive been looking everywhere for fishing maps/ nautical maps of the parry sound/pointe au baril part of georgian bay.... Anyone know where I can find any?  Thanks!
Checked it out, sucks you cant purchase online
I am not sure if these cover the area you want but you would probably know http://www.adventurefishingmaps.on.ca/sgb1.htm or possibly one of these http://www.fishingmapsplus.com/catalogue.htm   vance

Apperantly there is a place on front street in T O.Cant recall the name,not far from the station.Call the canadian coast gaurd station nearest to you.They are very helpfull for the info your seaking.Or even any noticle shop,they have noticle maps as well for different regions.

Not sure if these help... Located in Toronto   http://www.fedpubs.com/maps.htm     http://www.nauticalmind.com/_search.php?page=1&q=fishing+map+for+Georgian+bay     http://www.fedpubs.com/mpchrt/charts/georgianb.htm

If you are going to spend any time on Georgian Bay.. do yourself a favour and just buy the complete chart book for the area. Mine is the Lake Huron edition of Richardson's (including Georgian Bay and the North Channel).. from 20+ years ago.. not sure if they're still around or not, but I can guarantee the same rocks are still out there!!
but the water levels are just a wee bit lower than I remember in the old days
Few years ago I scanned all these charts, files are in printable page size good to bring on a boat instead of taking the chart. Pm me an email and I'll send you the files for that area.
